0:{"buildId":"I3GEKSVLVTWqxcEXDRaWq","rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"5S technique in ISO 9001 QMS implementation"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:31:54+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"In this article, we will show you the ways to combine and create the most effective way to obtain ISO 9001 with the 5S technique, which is also referred to as"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"5S technique in ISO 9001 QMS implementation"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"If you’re searching for the simplest way to effectively organize your workplace in order to comply with ISO 9001 certification standards, then you should understand what is 5s principle and how it can influence ISO 9001 QMS implementation in your organization and how it can fulfil the requirements of this ISO certification in UAE. If you want to acquire ISO 9001 certification for your organization to improve your overall business standards, then it is quite important to get to know about the famous 5S technique – a most popular and widely used concept for getting things organized so as to comply with the ISO 9001 QMS standards. In this article, we’ll show you the ways to combine and create the most effective way to obtain ISO 9001 with the 5S technique, which is also referred to as sensible housekeeping Practices"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"What is 5s technique and what does it stand for?"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"5s technique has its roots to Japan which encloses a list of 5 Japanese words that together represent a workplace organization methodology. Those 5 words are “Seiri” (Sort), “Seiton” (Set so as), “Seiso” (Shine), “Seiketsu” (Standardize), and “Shitsuke” (Sustain). This list describes the way to organize a workspace for effectiveness and efficiency by distinguishing and storing the materials used, removing surplus materials, clean up the work area, maintaining the work area and resources, and establishing a new order with procedure development, improved discipline and continuous improvement."}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Implementation of 5S technique"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"The implementation of the 5S technique should be carried out the following order:"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"“Seiri” (Sort) “Seiton” (Set in order) “Seiso” (Shine) “Seiketsu” (Standardize) “Shitsuke” (Sustain)"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"This exact order should be followed because the subsequent step is implemented on the basis or on the results of the previous step. For instance, you will be able to only set (Set in order) once you are clear about what must be used, where and how frequently (Sort). Check out the following example of implementing 5S and ISO 9001:"}],"$L2","$L3","$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7","$L8","$L9","$La","$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10"]}],"$L11"]}]}],["$L12"],"$L13"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
2:["$","p","8",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Sort"}]
3:["$","p","9",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"This principle suggests we must always only have with us what's relevant for your organization and business activity. If you take a look at your workplace, you might simply notice things that ought not to be there, that can create a lot of confusion and may act as an obstacle when least expected. For instance, in an organization, we may end up talking about obsolete product sample boxes, that are piled up and taking up enormous space in the workplace. Or in a manufacturing plant, we could be contemplating about obsolete tools lying around in the corners that are accumulating dirt and dust and attracting other obsolete tools, trash, broken equipment. Sort is the first S in the 5S which means that clearing out the workplace and discard anything that's not to be used at work."}]
4:["$","p","10",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Set in Order"}]
5:["$","p","11",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Now that we all know what's relevant for the workplace, the rule is One place for everything and everything in that place. Things and material that are required on a daily basis are permanently stored close to the place of use and with the perspective and visual identification for fast retrieval and storage. For instance, tools that are not used more than once a month doesn't get to be taking over the area close to the workplace every day. They can be kept elsewhere. Things and materials that are used once a year will be kept at the warehouse."}]
6:["$","p","12",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Shine"}]
7:["$","p","13",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"This could embody painting and enhancing lighting to set up a clean and tidy workplace all over the organization. It additionally might include repairing leaks, oiling screaky and highly frictional moving components, creating areas and flow methods clearly visible, making ways where there is a change to cut back waste production or devising efficiently waste management."}]
8:["$","p","14",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Standardize"}]
9:["$","p","15",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Until now, everything which has been implemented could be nothing more than an enormous cleansing exercise. One must think beyond an occasion and make it a daily task by standardizing routines, making work directions and instructions, devising regular training, utilizing visual signals as aids, installing photos and signboards as standards, promoting checklists to avoid forgetting important matters. In this manner, one can ensure that the previous steps become embedded within the work being performed."}]
a:["$","p","16",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Sustain"}]
b:["$","p","17",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Come up with new efficient and effective strategies and tricks to show what must be done and simply keep a keen eye to identify when something goes the wrong way. Devise ceaseless improvement of the 5S program."}]
c:["$","p","18",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Relation between ISO 9001 and 5S technique"}]
d:["$","p","19",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Applying 5S technique could be a pragmatic approach of implementing ISO 9001 QMS certification. Because ISO 9001 clauses 7.1.3 and 7.1.4 address Infrastructure, environment and surroundings for the Operation of Processes. In that line with clause 7.1.3, the organization's architecture and infrastructure that is required to produce a product or provide a service that ought to be maintained. Maintenance is often made sure by following sensible practices by operating and keeping infrastructure and its surroundings clean. For instance, the pile-up of scrap and dirt from production processes, and dirt on facilities will emanate enormous heat and therefore it will eventually breakdown the crucial equipment and components."}]
e:["$","p","20",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"The surroundings for the Operation of Processes (clause 7.1.4) is viewed as a group of human and physical factors. Work strategies are an example of human factors which will have an effect on the conformity of products and services. Physical factors like noise, vibration, heat, cleanliness and humidity, must be controlled and as a result of this, they will influence method efficacy or product or service conformity. Therefore, the principle of 5S technique should be taken into consideration while implementing ISO 9001 certification in Dubai, so that organizations can efficiently modify and arrange their work to design sensible operating procedures both for operation and cleaning. Also, periodic training and creating visual will assist to confirm the effective implementation of ISO 9001 QMS standard. These kinds of practice will ensure to take care of the principles and enhancements."}]
f:["$","p","21",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"ISO Certification in UAE is a most preferred Certification Standard by organizations in UAE from all sectors. WIZMS provides ISO Certificate in UAE for all major standards such as ISO 9001:2015, ISO 14001:2015, ISO 27001:2015, ISO 17025:2015, ISO 45001:2015 and more."}]
10:["$","p","22",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"WIZMS is the best ISO consultant in UAE and provides ISO consulting services in Dubai, Abu Dhabi, Sharjah, Ras al-Khaimah, Ajman, Al Ain and Fujairah. WIZMS ISO consultant in Dubai offers top-class ISO consultancy services including ISO Consulting, ISO Certification, ISO Training in UAE, Gap analysis, Documentation, Implementation, and ISO certification audits in UAE."}]
